## File Structure for Wargame Materials
```
phase7/scenarios/
├── WOPR_ENGINE_GUIDE.md         ← DS guide to running the WOPR engine
├── WORLD_MODEL_TEMPLATE.json    ← blank world state schema
├── ORBAT_BUILDER.md             ← how to build Red/Blue ORBATs
├── DETECTION_MODEL.md           ← fog of war physics rules
├── ADJUDICATION_TABLES.md       ← hit probability, EW effect, detection %
├── INJECT_LIBRARY.md            ← all 40+ injects, categorised
├── AAR_TEMPLATE.md              ← After Action Review output format
├── scn-01-permissive-isr/
│   ├── SCENARIO_BRIEF_DS.md     ← DS-eyes-only brief
│   ├── RED_FORCE_BRIEF.md       ← Red player brief (METT-TC, tasking)
│   ├── BLUE_FORCE_BRIEF.md      ← Blue player brief
│   ├── INJECT_TIMELINE.md       ← scripted inject schedule
│   └── ASSESSMENT_CRITERIA.md  ← decision point rubric
└── [repeat for scn-02 through scn-b]
```

## DS (Directing Staff) Rules
1. Never give either side information they couldn't realistically collect
2. The inject timer is DS's primary tool — don't let either side achieve comfortable certainty
3. Force decisions under time pressure — the clock runs even when players are deliberating
4. AAR is mandatory after every scenario — 30 min minimum
5. The learning objective is the *decision process*, not who wins
6. In the blind scenario (Day 5), DS is the only one who sees the full picture — maintain strict information separation

## Integration with Spectral Platform
The WOPR engine scenario data structure mirrors the Spectral platform's `scenario_templates` and `scenario_injects` tables. Scenario files designed here can be imported directly into Spectral via the Arena module. This is a deliberate architectural link — SPECTRAL PCM course → Spectral platform → same data model.
